programme.title: Growing Wild
programme.desc: To the uninitiated, a farmer's toil is never-ending, hard, and against the elements. To the initiated like Chris however, that's simply a misconception. Nature is elegant by design, everything has its place and purpose and nothing is wasted. There are lessons to be learnt from rain cycles and forest floor debris offer enriching take-aways.So the question is how? How do we apply these principles of nature to the green projects we bring into our non-wild, non-natural, personal spaces?

programme.desc: Eco-innovators introduce Zac and Darin to unique and cost-effective ways to address complex problems and help heal the environment.

programme.title: Man Eats Wild Episode 3
programme.desc: In the Kalahari Desert is an ancient tribe that has lived off the land since the beginning of man kind. These people are known as the Naru bushman. He joins the Naru people on a wild adventure in the Kalahari Desert in hope to prove himself and be accepted into this ancient tribe.

programme.title: PL STORIES Episode 18
programme.desc: He was a star of Australia's U23 and U17 teams and made his West Ham debut at just 18 years of age, but in 2011 Dylan Tombides life was turned upside down when he received a diagnosis of testicular cancer following a routine drug test during the Under-17 FIFA World Cup. Despite a courageous three-year battle, he tragically succumbed to the illness at the age of 20 in 2014.

programme.title: CLASSIC MATCH 14/15

programme.title: 1-TO-11

programme.title: PL STORIES Episode 8
programme.desc: We delve into the careers of some of the most enigmatic and unpredictable footballers to have graced the English top-flight in recent years and find out how they became "Premier League mavericks'. We get under the skin of what made these players notorious, controversial and flamboyant and the impact they had in their time in England.

programme.title: PL STORIES Episode 16
programme.desc: Kaoru Mitoma's football talent was evident from a young age in Japan, but when a professional opportunity came, he made the unexpected choice that left many surprised. This episode unravels the unique path that took Mitoma from university to the Premier League, where he's now making his mark on the world's toughest football stage.

programme.title: GOALS OF THE SEASON 2023/2024 (GB: HAALAND)
programme.desc: From free kicks to bicycle kicks, relive some of the most memorable strikes from 2023/24 in a Premier League season where there's been a record number of goals scored.

programme.title: PL REWIND Episode 4
programme.desc: In December 2023, Bournemouth v Luton is abandoned when Tom Lockyer faced a life-threatening situation on the pitch. He survived and watched the rematch, which turned into a Premier League classic. Andoni Iraola, Lewis Cook and Antoine Semenyo tell the story.

programme.title: PL REWIND Episode 3
programme.desc: In January 2023, Everton appointed Sean Dyche as manager, and gave him the critical task of keeping the club in the Premier League. We revisit the key moments of the Toffees' fight for survival, as told by the charismatic boss and his veteran captain Seamus Coleman.

programme.title: PL STORIES Episode 15
programme.desc: With over 200 appearances for Everton, Tim Cahill established himself as the high-energy midfielder who helped drive the side. For PL Stories this week, Cahill talks through his journey to the Premier League from battling his way to make it as a footballer in his native Australia, leaving home as a teenager and adapting to English life, scoring in a World Cup as well as the difficult decision to leave Goodison Park after 8 years.

programme.title: PL STORIES Episode 12
programme.desc: He was Villa's penalty saving hero in the 90s and the man tasked by Fergie to replace the legendary Peter Schmeichel at Manchester United. Former Australian number one, Mark Bosnich welcomes PL Stories down under as he reflects on his career in England's top-flight.

programme.title: PL STORIES Episode 50
programme.desc: From humble beginnings as a footballer in Melbourne to becoming Tottenham's manager, we chart the meteoric rise of Australian Ange Postecoglou. We speak to those that knew him best to find out what makes him tick and delve into his unique coaching style that has brought him success wherever he's been.
